ZONE 2 — INCLUDE GUARD
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  Prevents double inclusion. Always use #pragma once — it is shorter,
  correct on all modern compilers, and impossible to mis-type.
  Only fall back to #ifndef guards when targeting compilers that do not
  support #pragma once (rare embedded toolchains).

Template:
  #pragma once

  // Only use the macro form if the toolchain requires it:
  // #ifndef PROJECT_MODULE_NAME_HPP
  // #define PROJECT_MODULE_NAME_HPP
  // ... file body ...
  // #endif // PROJECT_MODULE_NAME_HPP

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ZONE 3 — INCLUDES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  Pull in every symbol this header directly uses. Never rely on transitive
  includes — if this file uses std::string, it includes <string> regardless
  of what else is included.

ORDERING RULE — strictly alphabetical within each group,
groups separated by one blank line:

  [GROUP A]  This module's own forward-declaration header (if it exists)
             #include "module_name_fwd.hpp"

  [GROUP B]  Other headers FROM THIS PROJECT (alphabetical, quoted)
             #include "core/error.hpp"
             #include "core/types.hpp"
             #include "network/address.hpp"

  [GROUP C]  Third-party library headers (alphabetical, quoted or angled)
             #include <spdlog/spdlog.h>
             #include <nlohmann/json.hpp>

  [GROUP D]  C++ Standard Library headers (alphabetical, angled)
             #include <algorithm>
             #include <chrono>
             #include <cstddef>
             #include <functional>
             #include <memory>
             #include <optional>
             #include <span>
             #include <stdexcept>
             #include <string>
             #include <string_view>
             #include <type_traits>
             #include <vector>

  [GROUP E]  C Standard Library headers (alphabetical, C++ form preferred)
             #include <cassert>
             #include <cstdint>
             #include <cstring>

PREFER FORWARDS OVER INCLUDES in headers:
  If you only use T*, T&, or std::unique_ptr<T> — forward declare T, do not
  include T's header. This reduces compilation fan-out.
  Exception: std::string, std::vector, STL types must be included not forwarded.

  Example:
    // Forward declare — do NOT include "network/socket.hpp" in this header
    namespace net { class Socket; }
    // Now you can declare:
    void process(const net::Socket& s);

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ZONE 4 — MACROS AND FEATURE FLAGS  (minimize — prefer constexpr)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  Macros that must be visible to all includers: platform detection, API
  export symbols, assertion wrappers. Keep to an absolute minimum.

Rules:
  - Never define a macro that could be a constexpr or enum class.
  - Prefix every macro with the project name: MYPROJ_ASSERT, MYPROJ_API.
  - Undef helper macros at the bottom of the header if they were only
    used within the header itself.
  - Document every macro with a Doxygen comment.

Template:
  // ── Platform export macro ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  #if defined(_WIN32) && defined(MYPROJ_BUILD_DLL)
  #  define MYPROJ_API __declspec(dllexport)
  #elif defined(_WIN32)
  #  define MYPROJ_API __declspec(dllimport)
  #else
  #  define MYPROJ_API __attribute__((visibility("default")))
  #endif

  /**
   * @def    MYPROJ_ASSERT(condition, message)
   * @brief  Debug-mode assertion with a descriptive message.
   *         Compiles to nothing in release builds.
   */
  #ifndef NDEBUG
  #  define MYPROJ_ASSERT(cond, msg)  \
       do { if (!(cond)) { throw std::logic_error((msg)); } } while(false)
  #else
  #  define MYPROJ_ASSERT(cond, msg)  do {} while(false)
  #endif

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ZONE 5 — NAMESPACE OPEN
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  Every project symbol lives inside at least one namespace.
  Never define anything at global scope except main() and extern "C" functions.

Rules:
  - Top-level namespace = project name or organization prefix: myproj::
  - Sub-namespaces = module name:  myproj::network::, myproj::core::
  - Never nest namespaces more than 3 levels deep.
  - Use C++17 nested namespace syntax: namespace myproj::network { ... }
  - Never put using namespace X; in a header at any scope.
  - using declarations inside a namespace body are allowed for long names
    needed repeatedly, documented with a comment.
  - Always put the closing brace comment: } // namespace myproj::network

Template:
  namespace myproj::network {

  // (all declarations go here)

  } // namespace myproj::network

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ZONE 6 — CONSTANTS AND TYPE ALIASES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  Named constants that belong to this module's interface. Type aliases that
  make the API easier to read and use. Always comes before class declarations.

Rules:
  - Use constexpr, not #define, for every constant.
  - Use enum class, not enum, for every enumeration.
  - Use using, not typedef, for every type alias.
  - Document every constant and alias with a Doxygen comment.
  - Group related constants inside a struct or inline namespace.

Template:
  /// Maximum number of simultaneous connections this module supports.
  inline constexpr std::size_t kMaxConnections = 1024;

  /// Default connection timeout in milliseconds.
  inline constexpr std::chrono::milliseconds kDefaultTimeout{5000};

  /**
   * @enum  ConnectionState
   * @brief Lifecycle states of a managed connection.
   */
  enum class ConnectionState : uint8_t {
      Disconnected = 0, ///< No active connection.
      Connecting   = 1, ///< Handshake in progress.
      Connected    = 2, ///< Fully established, ready to use.
      Closing      = 3, ///< Graceful shutdown in progress.
      Error        = 4, ///< Unrecoverable error state.
  };

  /// Convenience alias — callers write Port instead of std::uint16_t.
  using Port    = std::uint16_t;
  using Address = std::string;

