ZONE 8 — FREE FUNCTION DECLARATIONS  (if this is a function-based API)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  For C-style or utility APIs that are not member functions.
  Ordered from most important / most frequently called to least.

Rules:
  - Every function has a full Doxygen block: @brief, @param, @return,
    @throws, @pre, @post, @note, @see.
  - Mark noexcept when you guarantee no exception will propagate.
  - Mark [[nodiscard]] on every function whose return value must not be ignored.
  - Mark [[deprecated("use X instead")]] on functions being phased out.

Template:
  /**
   * @brief  Resolves a hostname to an IP address string.
   *
   * @param  hostname  The DNS name to resolve. Must not be empty.
   * @param  timeout   Maximum time to wait for DNS response.
   *                   Pass std::nullopt to use kDefaultTimeout.
   *
   * @return  Resolved IPv4 or IPv6 address string.
   *
   * @throws  std::invalid_argument  if hostname is empty.
   * @throws  ResolveError           if DNS lookup fails or times out.
   *
   * @pre   hostname is a valid DNS label (RFC 1035).
   * @post  Return value is a valid IP address string parseable by inet_pton.
   *
   * @thread-safety  Safe to call from multiple threads concurrently.
   */
  [[nodiscard]]
  Address resolve(std::string_view hostname,
                  std::optional<std::chrono::milliseconds> timeout = std::nullopt);

