ZONE 9 — CLASS / STRUCT DECLARATIONS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  The primary type(s) this header provides.
  Order within a header: base classes / interfaces first, then concrete classes.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CLASS INTERNAL LAYOUT — ALWAYS IN THIS EXACT ORDER:
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  [1]  Class-level Doxygen comment (what it is, design pattern, thread safety)
  [2]  public: section
       [2a]  Nested type aliases and enumerations
       [2b]  Nested classes and structs (if small; otherwise separate header)
       [2c]  Static constants belonging to the public interface
       [2d]  Constructors (default, parameter, conversion — all explicit unless noted)
       [2e]  Destructor
       [2f]  Copy constructor + copy assignment  (or = delete with comment)
       [2g]  Move constructor + move assignment  (or = delete with comment)
       [2h]  swap() friend function if Rule of Five is implemented
       [2i]  Comparison operators (==, !=, <, >, <=, >= or <=>)
       [2j]  Conversion operators (explicit only, documented)
       [2k]  Primary public methods — in call-order: setup → use → teardown
       [2l]  Static factory methods (if construction is complex)
       [2m]  Observer/callback registration methods
       [2n]  Accessors (getters) — all const
       [2o]  Mutators (setters) — all documented with invariants they maintain
       [2p]  Diagnostic / debug methods (dump(), to_string(), operator<<)
  [3]  protected: section  (only if designed for inheritance)
       [3a]  Protected constructors (if abstract base or NVI base)
       [3b]  Protected virtual methods (override points)
       [3c]  Protected helper methods
  [4]  private: section
       [4a]  Private type aliases used in implementation
       [4b]  Private helper methods (declared here, defined in .cpp)
       [4c]  Private static methods
       [4d]  DATA MEMBERS — always last, always private, always trailing underscore
  [5]  Non-member functions that are part of the class's interface:
       operator<<, swap(), make_X() factories — declared outside the class,
       in the same namespace, with a blank line between the closing brace and them.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
FULL CLASS TEMPLATE:
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  /**
   * @class   ClassName
   * @brief   One sentence: what this class represents or does.
   *
   * DESCRIPTION
   * -----------
   * 2–4 sentences: responsibilities, lifecycle, design rationale.
   * Name the design pattern if one is applied.
   *
   * INVARIANTS
   * ----------
   * - List every class invariant that is always true after construction.
   * - E.g.: "buffer_.size() <= capacity_ at all times."
   *
   * OWNERSHIP
   * ---------
   * - Does this class own its data? Shared ownership? Non-owning observer?
   *
   * THREAD SAFETY
   * -------------
   * - const methods: thread-safe / not thread-safe
   * - non-const methods: require external sync / internally synchronized
   *
   * @tparam T  (if template) Constraint: must satisfy std::copyable.
   */
  class ClassName {
  public:
      // ── Nested types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /// Alias for the element type managed by this class.
      using value_type      = int;
      using size_type       = std::size_t;
      using iterator        = value_type*;
      using const_iterator  = const value_type*;

      /**
       * @struct Config
       * @brief  Construction-time configuration for ClassName.
       *         Separates mandatory from optional parameters cleanly.
       */
      struct Config {
          std::size_t             initial_capacity = 16;    ///< Starting allocation size.
          std::chrono::seconds    timeout          {30};    ///< Operation timeout.
          bool                    enable_logging   = false; ///< Write debug logs.
      };

      // ── Static constants ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /// Maximum allowed capacity. Attempting to exceed this throws std::length_error.
      static constexpr size_type kMaxCapacity = 1'000'000;

      // ── Constructors ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Default constructor. Creates an empty, valid object.
       * @post   size() == 0 && capacity() == Config{}.initial_capacity
       */
      ClassName();

      /**
       * @brief  Constructs with explicit configuration.
       * @param  cfg  Configuration struct. All fields have documented defaults.
       * @throws std::invalid_argument if cfg.initial_capacity == 0 or
       *                               cfg.initial_capacity > kMaxCapacity.
       */
      explicit ClassName(const Config& cfg);

      // ── Destructor ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Releases all resources owned by this object.
       * @note   Does NOT throw. Any pending operations are cancelled cleanly.
       */
      ~ClassName();

      // ── Copy semantics ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Copy constructor — deep copy.
       * @post   *this == other but this->data() != other.data() (independent copy)
       */
      ClassName(const ClassName& other);

      /**
       * @brief  Copy assignment — copy-and-swap idiom for strong exception safety.
       */
      ClassName& operator=(const ClassName& other);

      // ── Move semantics ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Move constructor — O(1), leaves other in a valid empty state.
       * @post   other.size() == 0 after this call.
       */
      ClassName(ClassName&& other) noexcept;

      /**
       * @brief  Move assignment.
       * @post   other.size() == 0 after this call.
       */
      ClassName& operator=(ClassName&& other) noexcept;

      /**
       * @brief  Swaps two objects without copying. Used by copy-and-swap.
       * @note   noexcept — swap never fails.
       */
      friend void swap(ClassName& a, ClassName& b) noexcept;

      // ── Comparison operators ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Two ClassName objects are equal if they contain the same
       *         elements in the same order.
       */
      friend bool operator==(const ClassName& a, const ClassName& b) noexcept;
      friend bool operator!=(const ClassName& a, const ClassName& b) noexcept;

      // ── Primary interface ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Appends a value to the end of the collection.
       *
       * Amortized O(1). May reallocate internal storage if capacity is exceeded.
       *
       * @param  value  The value to append.
       * @throws std::length_error if size() == kMaxCapacity before the call.
       *
       * @post   size() == old_size + 1
       * @post   back() == value
       */
      void push_back(value_type value);

      /**
       * @brief  Constructs a new element in-place at the end.
       *         More efficient than push_back when constructing from arguments.
       *
       * @param  args  Constructor arguments forwarded to value_type.
       * @return       Reference to the newly constructed element.
       */
      template<typename... Args>
      value_type& emplace_back(Args&&... args);

      /**
       * @brief  Removes the last element.
       * @throws std::underflow_error if the collection is empty.
       * @post   size() == old_size - 1
       */
      void pop_back();

      /**
       * @brief  Removes all elements. Does not release allocated memory.
       * @post   size() == 0 && capacity() == old_capacity
       */
      void clear() noexcept;

      /**
       * @brief  Ensures at least new_cap elements can be stored without reallocation.
       * @throws std::length_error if new_cap > kMaxCapacity.
       * @post   capacity() >= new_cap
       */
      void reserve(size_type new_cap);

      // ── Accessors ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Accesses element at position pos with bounds checking.
       * @throws std::out_of_range if pos >= size().
       */
      [[nodiscard]] value_type&       at(size_type pos);
      [[nodiscard]] const value_type& at(size_type pos) const;

      /// Unchecked element access. UB if pos >= size().
      [[nodiscard]] value_type&       operator[](size_type pos) noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] const value_type& operator[](size_type pos) const noexcept;

      [[nodiscard]] value_type&       front();
      [[nodiscard]] const value_type& front() const;
      [[nodiscard]] value_type&       back();
      [[nodiscard]] const value_type& back()  const;

      [[nodiscard]] iterator        begin()  noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] const_iterator  begin()  const noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] const_iterator  cbegin() const noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] iterator        end()    noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] const_iterator  end()    const noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] const_iterator  cend()   const noexcept;

      [[nodiscard]] bool        empty()    const noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] size_type   size()     const noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] size_type   capacity() const noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] value_type* data()     noexcept;
      [[nodiscard]] const value_type* data() const noexcept;

      // ── Diagnostic ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      /**
       * @brief  Returns a human-readable description of the object state.
       *         Used for debugging and logging — not for serialization.
       */
      [[nodiscard]] std::string to_string() const;

  protected:
      // Protected section exists ONLY if this class is a designed base.
      // Document what a subclass is expected to override.

  private:
      // ── Private helpers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      void grow();                        // Reallocates to 2x current capacity.
      void check_not_empty() const;       // Throws if size_ == 0.
      void check_bounds(size_type) const; // Throws if pos >= size_.

      // ── Data members — always last, always private ────────────────────────────
      value_type* data_     = nullptr;  ///< Heap-allocated element storage.
      size_type   size_     = 0;        ///< Number of live elements.
      size_type   capacity_ = 0;        ///< Total allocated slots.
  };

  // ── Non-member interface functions ───────────────────────────────────────────

  /**
   * @brief  Stream insertion — formats object for human-readable output.
   * @note   Does NOT format for serialization. Output format may change.
   */
  std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const ClassName& obj);

