ZONE 10 — TEMPLATE AND INLINE DEFINITIONS  (small bodies only)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Purpose:
  Template function bodies MUST be visible in every translation unit that
  instantiates them, so they live in the header. Inline bodies shorter than
  3 lines may also live here. Larger template bodies go in a _inl.hpp file.

Rule: if the body is > 5 lines, put it in a _inl.hpp and include it at the
      bottom of this header.

Template:
  template<typename... Args>
  inline ClassName::value_type& ClassName::emplace_back(Args&&... args) {
      if (size_ == capacity_) grow();
      return *new (data_ + size_++) value_type(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
  }

